  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Preparedness to Ebola Virus Diseases (EVD) Outbreak in Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is part of a broader programme which will contribute to the scaling-up of risk communication and community engagement, infection prevention and control, and water, sanitation, and hygiene interventions in order to reduce mortality and morbidity and the further spread of EVD. The programme will also enhance the capacity of immigration officials and strengthen facilities in points of entry with DRC to adequately manage large cross-border flow by empowering selected border posts with essential equipment and infrastructure rehabilitation.</narrative>
  </description>
